```

Note: The treemap node fill colors (from `pastelPalette`) will need darkened variants in dark mode. Apply `filter: brightness(0.55) saturate(1.2)` on `.treemap-node` and `.treemap-group` in dark mode, which converts the light pastels to suitable dark-mode fills while preserving color identity. The text color for treemap nodes should switch to `#e0e0e0` in dark mode.

#### 4e. JavaScript: Squarified treemap algorithm + rendering

Add inside the IIFE (after the initial package map render block, ~line 448). Key components:

1. **Data**: `var pkgMapData = {{.PackageMapJSON}};` — Inline the JSON tree data.

2. **Squarify algorithm**: `function squarify(nodes, rect)` — Implements the squarified treemap algorithm:
   - Sort nodes by value descending
   - Iteratively place nodes in rows, choosing horizontal/vertical layout based on which produces better (closer to 1:1) aspect ratios
   - Returns array of `{x, y, w, h, node}` positioned rectangles

3. **Render function**: `function renderTreemap(container, nodes, rect, depth, colorIdx)` — Recursively renders the treemap:
   - Leaf nodes: creates `div.treemap-node` with `span.tm-name` + `span.tm-stats`, colored from pastel palette
   - Parent nodes: creates `div.treemap-group` with `div.treemap-group-label`, recursively renders children in sub-rectangle (minus header height ~18px)
   - Sets `position: absolute` with `left/top/width/height` from algorithm output
   - Hides labels when rectangles are too small (< 30px height: hide stats; < 20px: hide name)
   - Attaches `mouseenter`/`mouseleave` events for tooltip

4. **Layout function**: `function layoutTreemap()` — Reads `#pkgmap-html-viewport` dimensions, clears `#pkgmap-html-container`, calls squarify + renderTreemap.

5. **Lazy rendering** — Only render when the tab is first activated. Add `var pkgMapHtmlRendered = false;` flag (like the existing `pkgMapRendered` flag at line 356).

6. **ResizeObserver** on `#pkgmap-html-viewport` to call `layoutTreemap()` on size change (debounced at 150ms).

7. **Pastel palette** — Same 10 colors as the Go-side `pastelPalette` (lines 142-153), as a JS array of `{fill, stroke, text}` objects.

8. **Tooltip** — Create a single shared `div.treemap-tooltip` (hidden by default) appended to `document.body`. On `mouseenter` of any `.treemap-node`, show tooltip near cursor with: package full path, N interfaces, M types. On `mouseleave`, hide. On `mousemove`, reposition.

9. **Cap nesting depth at 3** — Flatten deeper packages into the third level to avoid too-small sub-rectangles.

#### 4f. Update `getActiveContainer()` (line 637)
Add case for the new tab:
```js
function getActiveContainer() {
  if (currentTab === pkgmap) return document.getElementById(pkgmap-container);
  if (currentTab === pkgmap-html) return document.getElementById(pkgmap-html-container);
  if (currentTab === ifaces) return document.getElementById(ifaces-diagram-container);
  return document.getElementById(impls-diagram-container);
}
```

#### 4g. Update `switchTab()` function (line 418)
Add lazy-render trigger for the new tab:
```js
if (tab === pkgmap-html && !pkgMapHtmlRendered) {
  layoutTreemap();
  pkgMapHtmlRendered = true;
}
```

#### 4h. Update "Copy Source" button (line 660)
When `currentTab === pkgmap-html`, generate a text representation from the package map data instead of Mermaid source:
```
internal/analyzer: 2 ifaces, 5 types
internal/server: 1 iface, 3 types
...
```
Also update the button title dynamically: set `title="Copy Package List"` when on the HTML tab, `title="Copy Mermaid Source"` otherwise. Do this in `switchTab()`.

#### 4i. Keep `/mermaid.md` endpoint unchanged
No changes — it still serves Mermaid text for the original Package Map tab.

## Dependencies

- **No external packages**. The squarified treemap algorithm is vanilla JS within the template.
- Internal dependency on `analyzer.Result` (unchanged).
- `GeneratePackageMapMermaid()` is still called — no existing code removed.

## Edge Cases and Error Handling

1. **Empty result (no packages)**: Show a centered "No packages found" message in the treemap viewport.
2. **Single package**: Treemap degenerates to a single rectangle filling the container. Works naturally.
3. **Very many packages (50+)**: Small rectangles may not fit labels. Hide `.tm-stats` when height < 30px, hide `.tm-name` when < 20px. Tooltip on hover shows all info.
4. **Very deep hierarchy (5+ levels)**: Cap nesting at 3 levels — flatten deeper packages into the third level.
5. **Packages with 0 interfaces and 0 types**: Use `value = 1` so they are still visible.
6. **Window resize**: `ResizeObserver` recalculates layout. Debounce at 150ms.
7. **Dark mode**: Use CSS `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` overrides with `filter: brightness(0.55) saturate(1.2)` on treemap nodes and lighter border/text colors.

## Testing Strategy

### Automated tests (in `goifaces/internal/integration_test.go`)

1. **`TestPreparePackageMapData`** — Unit test for the new function:
   - Multi-package input produces correct tree structure
   - Values are computed correctly (sum of children for parents, max(ifaces+types, 1) for leaves)
   - Common prefix is stripped
   - Hierarchy is correctly nested

2. **`TestPreparePackageMapDataEmpty`** — Empty result produces nil/empty slice.

3. **`TestPreparePackageMapDataSinglePackage`** — Single package produces a single root node.

4. **Existing tests pass unchanged** — All existing tests for `GeneratePackageMapMermaid()`, `TestPackageMapMultiPackage`, `TestPackageMapRelativePaths`, etc. must still pass since that code is untouched.

### Manual verification

1. Run `go run . <repo-path>` and open the browser
2. Verify the "Package Map" (Mermaid) tab still works exactly as before
3. Click "Package Map (html)" tab — verify treemap fills the viewport
4. Verify packages are correctly labeled with name + counts
5. Verify hover shows tooltip with full package path
6. Verify zoom in/out/reset works on the new tab
7. Verify window resize recalculates treemap layout
8. Verify "Copy Source" copies text list on the HTML tab and Mermaid source on the Package Map tab
9. Verify `/mermaid.md` endpoint still returns Mermaid source
10. Verify Implementations and Interfaces tabs are unaffected
11. Verify dark mode renders treemap with appropriate colors

## Summary

Add 'Clear' (deselect all) and 'All' (select all) buttons to the sidebar of both the Interfaces and Implementations tabs. Currently users can only toggle checkboxes one at a time — these buttons provide quick bulk selection controls. The buttons should appear at the top of each entity-list sidebar, above the checkbox items.

## Technical Approach

All changes are in a single file: `goifaces/internal/server/server.go`, which contains the entire UI (HTML template, CSS, and JavaScript) as a Go string constant.

The approach is straightforward DOM manipulation following existing patterns:
- Add a small button bar (`<div>`) at the top of each `entity-list` sidebar
- Wire up click handlers that programmatically check/uncheck all checkboxes for that tab
- Call the existing `onSelectionChange()` after toggling to trigger diagram re-render
- No Go backend changes needed — this is purely client-side UI

### Why this approach
- Minimal change surface (one file)
- Follows existing patterns: the codebase already uses vanilla JS DOM manipulation (no framework)
- Reuses existing `onSelectionChange()` for state management — no new state tracking needed
- The checkbox state lives in the DOM (via `.impl-cb:checked` / `.iface-cb:checked` queries), so programmatically setting `.checked` and calling `onSelectionChange()` is the natural approach

## Files to Create

None.

## Files to Modify

### `goifaces/internal/server/server.go`

Three areas of changes within the `interactiveHTMLTemplate` string constant:

#### 1. CSS — Add button bar styles (~line 160, after `.entity-list` styles)

Add styles for the bulk action button bar inside the sidebar:

```css
.entity-list-actions {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.25rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
}

.entity-list-actions button {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 0.3rem 0.5rem;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 4px;
  background-color: #f8f9fa;
  color: #212529;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.15s;
}

.entity-list-actions button:hover {
  background-color: #e9ecef;
}
```

Also add dark-mode overrides inside the existing `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block:

```css
.entity-list-actions {
  border-bottom-color: #444;
}

.entity-list-actions button {
  background-color: #333;
  color: #e0e0e0;
  border-color: #555;
}

.entity-list-actions button:hover {
  background-color: #444;
